  "title": "feat(middleware): add unuse method",
  "body": "<!--\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\n-->\n\n**Summary**\n\nThis PR adds `unuse` method to unsubscribe and remove middleware that was added to InstantSearch.\n\nSo far, `this.middleware` in InstantSearch instance used to be `MiddlewareDefinition[]`.\nSince this PR, it's now `Array<{ middleware: Middleware, middlewareDefinition: MiddlewareDefinition }>`.\n(By the way, `type Middleware = (options: MiddlewareOptions) => MiddlewareDefinition;`)\n\nThe reason is, when we add a middleware, we pass a `middleware: Middleware`. However, we invokes the function and stores the middlewareDefinition. And here we loses the `middleware`. Later when we want to unuse the middleware, we have no way to match between the middleware and its middlewareDefinition.\nTo keep the connection, we're storing both of them. It doesn't chage any public API.\n\n**Result**\n\nNow we can unuse (unsubscribe) middlewares.",
